it's the high school, do you?

250
00:12:46,416 --> 00:12:47,916
Of course!

251
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:50,000
It's gotta be from one of those
girls at the school festival!

252
00:12:50,083 --> 00:12:51,166
Awesome!

253
00:12:51,250 --> 00:12:52,458
[FATHER 3A] Incredible!

254
00:12:52,541 --> 00:12:55,791
I don't even sense the chi,
and he can see it!

255
00:12:55,875 --> 00:12:57,416
Attaboy, slugger!

256
00:12:57,500 --> 00:12:59,416
You've surpassed your old man!

257
00:12:59,500 --> 00:13:01,166
Good on ya!

258
00:13:02,833 --> 00:13:06,583
[STUDENTS cheer and applaud]

259
00:13:06,666 --> 00:13:08,791
[ROKA] Hm.

260
00:13:08,875 --> 00:13:10,958
[KAZAMA grunts]

261
00:13:11,041 --> 00:13:12,916
[INADA] So, it's all
come down to this.

262
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:15,583
One winner-takes-all
round of the King's Game.

263
00:13:15,666 --> 00:13:17,375
Here're the rules, people.

264
00:13:17,458 --> 00:13:19,166
You take a bunch
of popsicle sticks,

265
00:13:19,250 --> 00:13:21,083
number 'em according
to how many players,

266
00:13:21,166 --> 00:13:23,166
and make one the King stick.

267
00:13:23,250 --> 00:13:25,541
Pull the winning stick,
and you're the King.

268
00:13:25,625 --> 00:13:27,250
Everyone else is a commoner.

269
00:13:27,333 --> 00:13:30,541
And the King can boss around
the commoners however he wants!

270
00:13:30,625 --> 00:13:33,083
But, seeing as how we
only have two players,

271
00:13:33,166 --> 00:13:35,708
we'll just skip the whole
bossing 'em around part.

272
00:13:35,791 --> 00:13:39,375
Whoever pulls the King stick
wins the whole thing.

273
00:13:39,458 --> 00:13:41,000
Look at those
game-faces!

274
00:13:41,083 --> 00:13:42,916
These two are out for blood!

275
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:44,666
He's cracking his knuckles!

276
00:13:44,750 --> 00:13:47,041
Not strictly necessary for
pulling a stick out of a can,

277
00:13:47,125 --> 00:13:48,833
but hey, whatever!

278
00:13:48,916 --> 00:13:51,416
Whoa, and she's
making a rice-ball!

279
00:13:51,500 --> 00:13:52,791
Are you serious?

280
00:13:52,875 --> 00:13:54,458
Food at a time like this?

281
00:13:54,541 --> 00:13:56,375
She's cool as a
cucumber, this one!

282
00:13:56,458 --> 00:13:57,958
Unbelievable!

283
00:13:58,041 --> 00:14:02,750
[BIRDIE 3A chirps]

284
00:14:02,833 --> 00:14:04,541
--[YAMADA] Ah!
--Chill out, Yamada.

285
00:14:04,625 --> 00:14:06,541
It's only a round
of the King's Game.

286
00:14:06,625 --> 00:14:08,458
Yeah. Yeah, you're right.

287
00:14:08,541 --> 00:14:10,333
I would hunker down
a bit, though,

288
00:14:10,416 --> 00:14:12,500
if it's all the same to you.

289
00:14:13,958 --> 00:14:15,875
No point losing your head.

290
00:14:15,958 --> 00:14:19,041
Uh... But I need my head!

291
00:14:19,125 --> 00:14:20,500
Is this low enough?

292
00:14:20,583 --> 00:14:22,833
Perfect.
You should be safe now.

293
00:14:22,916 --> 00:14:26,375
An' Roka will be able to
reach the sticks easier.

294
00:14:28,250 --> 00:14:29,208
[ROKA] Gulp!

295
00:14:29,291 --> 00:14:31,041
I'm onto you, pal.

296
00:14:31,125 --> 00:14:32,916
You wanted Yamada
to crouch down

297
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:35,166
just so you could peek
at the can, didn't you?

298
00:14:35,250 --> 00:14:38,000
[BIRDIE 3A chirps]

299
00:14:38,083 --> 00:14:39,958
Wow!

300
00:14:40,041 --> 00:14:42,875
So, who do you think's gonna
walk away as the winner?

301
00:14:42,958 --> 00:14:46,000
Huh? Uh, it's anybody's game.

302
00:14:46,083 --> 00:14:48,875
Skill is not a factor,
it all comes down to luck.

303
00:14:48,958 --> 00:14:50,000
Huh?

304
00:14:50,083 --> 00:14:51,500
There's something
on the ground there.

305
00:14:51,583 --> 00:14:53,166
I think Roka dropped it.

306
00:14:53,250 --> 00:14:54,750
What is that?

307
00:14:54,833 --> 00:14:55,375
Huh?!

308
00:14:55,458 --> 00:14:56,583
It couldn't be!

309
00:14:56,666 --> 00:14:58,166
Nuh-uh! No way!

310
00:14:58,250 --> 00:15:00,291
It can't possibly be a-a...!

311
00:15:00,375 --> 00:15:03,583
Holy crapcakes, it is!
That is the Silver Angel!

312
00:15:03,666 --> 00:15:04,958
What's wrong,
Four-Eyes?

313
00:15:05,041 --> 00:15:06,958
Bad case of candy envy?

314
00:15:07,041 --> 00:15:09,208
[ROKA] Oh yeah.
I won this yesterday

315
00:15:09,291 --> 00:15:11,250
when I happened to buy
some chocolate on a whim.

316
00:15:11,333 --> 00:15:12,541
[INADA] No way!

317
00:15:12,625 --> 00:15:14,583
You're saying you weren't
even trying to win?

318
00:15:14,666 --> 00:15:16,666
Check it. You know
what that means.

319
00:15:16,750 --> 00:15:18,791
Roka must have some
incredible luck!

320
00:15:18,875 --> 00:15:21,958
Yeah. It's not lookin'
so good for Kazama!

321
00:15:22,041 --> 00:15:25,541
[KAZAMA] Hmph. I dunno why
you guys are freaking out.

322
00:15:25,625 --> 00:15:26,875
Think of it this way.

323
00:15:26,958 --> 00:15:28,125
[ROKA] Hm?

324
00:15:28,208 --> 00:15:30,583
Winnin' that angel was
pretty lucky, no doubt.

325
00:15:30,666 --> 00:15:33,416
But doesn't that mean you're
all outta luck right now?

326
00:15:33,500 --> 00:15:35,583
[CHITOSE]
He spun it like a pro!

327
00:15:35,666 --> 00:15:38,375
Hold on.
Good luck can run out?

328
00:15:38,458 --> 00:15:40,208
Sounds like a cliché
that would be used

329
00:15:40,291 --> 00:15:42,083
by someone who's unlucky.

330
00:15:42,166 --> 00:15:44,041
Your logic does not apply to me.

331
00:15:44,125 --> 00:15:45,958
[SHINONOME, JIJOU and ISLE]
Roka's such a bad-ass!

332
00:15:46,041 --> 00:15:48,833
Okay. I'm not denying
the girl is lucky.

333
00:15:48,916 --> 00:15:51,375
Kinda reminds me...

334
00:15:51,458 --> 00:15:53,333
...of something that happened
back at New Year's.

335
00:15:53,416 --> 00:15:56,166
[INADA] He's pulling
a flashback?

336
00:15:56,250 --> 00:15:58,208
[KAZAMA] I was thinkin' about
hittin' the local shrine,

337
00:15:58,291 --> 00:16:01,291
so I was walkin' around
town with my little sister.

338
00:16:01,375 --> 00:16:02,916
Just then!

339
00:16:04,416 --> 00:16:06,416
Hey, that's...!

340
00:16:09,125 --> 00:16:10,500
[SAKURA, CHITOSE, and INADA]
Wait, you found...!

341
00:16:10,583 --> 00:16:13,291
[GROUP] Little Tama's New Year's
money from Grandpa?

342
00:16:13,375 --> 00:16:16,750
Let the record show that there
was 10,000 yen in that envelope!

343
00:16:16,833 --> 00:16:18,083
[INADA]
Wow, little Tama!

344
00:16:18,166 --> 00:16:20,333
Grandpa loves you a crap-ton!

345
00:16:20,416 --> 00:16:21,875
I get it.

346
00:16:21,958 --> 00:16:23,625
You're saying that you were
pretty lucky to have found that

347
00:16:23,708 --> 00:16:27,458
10,000 yen lying on the
sidewalk, is that it, Kazama?

348
00:16:27,541 --> 00:16:28,625
No Roka!

349
00:16:28,708 --> 00:16:30,166
That wasn't the
end of the story.

350
00:16:30,250 --> 00:16:31,375
[ROKA gasps]

351
00:16:31,458 --> 00:16:33,500
C'mon. Losing that much
money would be like

352
00:16:33,583 --> 00:16:36,541
the end of the world
to a little kid, right?

353
00:16:36,625 --> 00:16:39,750
Plus, I wanted to set a
good example for my sister.

354
00:16:39,833 --> 00:16:43,500
So, I brought it to the cops.

355
00:16:43,583 --> 00:16:45,583
Dammit, Kazama!

356
00:16:45,666 --> 00:16:49,125
You're such a good brother,
you, got me right in the feels!

357
00:16:49,208 --> 00:16:52,666
[CHITOSE] Whatever--he's
still a juvenile delinquent.

358
00:16:52,750 --> 00:16:54,083
[KAZAMA] Did you know?

359
00:16:54,166 --> 00:16:56,666
If an item sits in the
lost-and-found for half a year

360
00:16:56,750 --> 00:16:58,583
without anyone coming to get it,

361
00:16:58,666 --> 00:17:02,208
the guy who dropped it off
can claim it as his own?

362
00:17:02,291 --> 00:17:05,375
That fateful day was
six long months ago.

363
00:17:05,458 --> 00:17:06,750
And now!

364
00:17:06,833 --> 00:17:08,750
I swear unto all of you!

365
00:17:08,833 --> 00:17:12,500
I am not gonna go
back for that money!

366
00:17:12,583 --> 00:17:14,333
[INADA] Did he just say

367
00:17:14,416 --> 00:17:17,208
he's gonna pretend that he
never found the 10,000 yen?

368
00:17:17,291 --> 00:17:20,166
And take all that luck back
into his system for this!

369
00:17:20,250 --> 00:17:22,291
[INADA] Little Tama,
if you're out there,

370
00:17:22,375 --> 00:17:24,000
go to the cops and
get your cash!

371
00:17:24,083 --> 00:17:25,916
Things are getting
serious, you guys!

372
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:28,375
I, I can actually
see their luck!

373
00:17:28,458 --> 00:17:31,125
It's swirling around
them like a cyclone!

374
00:17:31,208 --> 00:17:32,625
[CHITOSE]
Huh, luck is a lot darker

375
00:17:32,708 --> 00:17:34,416
than I thought it would be.

376
00:17:34,500 --> 00:17:36,833
[INADA] Poor Yamada's
at the breaking point!

377
00:17:36,916 --> 00:17:40,416
Stay strong, ya big lug!

378
00:17:40,500 --> 00:17:42,041
I'm glad that I'm
playing someone

379
00:17:42,125 --> 00:17:44,083
who'll give it their all.

380
00:17:44,166 --> 00:17:46,416
Right back atcha.

381
00:17:46,500 --> 00:17:48,000
Hey Kazama.

382
00:17:48,083 --> 00:17:49,958
Do you mind if I
ask you something?

383
00:17:50,041 --> 00:17:51,875
[KAZAMA] Hm?

384
00:17:51,958 --> 00:17:53,958
I want know what you
plan to do with my bag

385
00:17:54,041 --> 00:17:56,083
should you win it today.

386
00:17:56,166 --> 00:17:59,375
[KAZAMA]
I forgot about the bag.

387
00:17:59,458 --> 00:18:03,000
I'd keep it with me as proof
that I won the game, you know?

388
00:18:03,083 --> 00:18:06,166
It'd be a trophy, so
I'd take good care of it.

389
00:18:10,041 --> 00:18:12,125
[TAKAO groans]

390
00:18:14,125 --> 00:18:16,750
[ROKA] In that case, I'm okay
with you having it.

391
00:18:16,833 --> 00:18:18,541
That was easy enough.

392
00:18:18,625 --> 00:18:20,708
Throwing in the towel, huh?

393
00:18:20,791 --> 00:18:21,916
Not that I blame ya,
I am pretty--

394
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:23,541
[ROKA]
Let's do this.

395
00:18:27,375 --> 00:18:30,708
[SAKURA] The only bag he's
getting today is a body-bag!

396
00:18:34,708 --> 00:18:36,500
Serves him right!

397
00:18:38,875 --> 00:18:41,333
Hey, guys, we're gonna
have to clear out

398
00:18:41,416 --> 00:18:43,208
of the stadium pretty soon.

399
00:18:43,291 --> 00:18:46,250
You wanna do us a favor and pull
the friggin' sticks already?

400
00:18:51,208 --> 00:18:53,708
What is he doing?

401
00:18:53,791 --> 00:18:54,916
[ROKA grunts]

402
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:57,083
[INADA] He... He's!

403
00:18:57,166 --> 00:18:59,458
He's holding down her
stick with his own!

404
00:18:59,541 --> 00:19:02,708
[KAZAMA] Heh. Yeah, right!

405
00:19:02,791 --> 00:19:05,916
There's no way I'm leaving
it to luck after all this!

406
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:09,958
If you wanna be the king,
you gotta reach out and take it!

407
00:19:10,041 --> 00:19:11,125
[ROKA gasps]

408
00:19:13,708 --> 00:19:16,208
[KAZAMA] Whoever grabs it first
is the winner, got it?

409
00:19:16,291 --> 00:19:17,458
[SAKURA and CHITOSE gasps]

410
00:19:17,541 --> 00:19:19,708
Sudden death!

411
00:19:19,791 --> 00:19:21,708
Roka, it's a trap!

412
00:19:22,916 --> 00:19:24,083
[ROKA gasps]

413
00:19:24,166 --> 00:19:25,208
[KAZAMA] Heh.

414
00:19:25,291 --> 00:19:26,625
What just happened?

415
00:19:26,708 --> 00:19:28,333
I didn't see anything
but a big blur!

416
00:19:28,416 --> 00:19:29,458
He dodged the bag!

417
00:19:29,541 --> 00:19:31,208
He must have known
it was coming!

418
00:19:31,291 --> 00:19:34,625
If I didn't, I couldn't
have dodged it!

419
00:19:34,708 --> 00:19:36,833
Ah! He's heading for!

420
00:19:36,916 --> 00:19:38,833
[GROUP] Yamada!

421
00:19:38,916 --> 00:19:40,166
[KAZAMA] Heh.

422
00:19:40,250 --> 00:19:41,291
[KAZAMA yells]

423
00:19:41,375 --> 00:19:43,916
[GROUP] He used him
as a springboard?

424
00:20:00,250 --> 00:20:02,916
Well, looks like
I'm the king.

425
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:06,625
[ROKA grunts]

426
00:20:08,125 --> 00:20:12,500
Wait, he...
Did you just... Huh?

427
00:20:12,583 --> 00:20:14,625
Ladies and gentlemen,
we have an upset!

428
00:20:14,708 --> 00:20:17,125
Kazama wins!

429
00:20:17,208 --> 00:20:24,916
[STUDENTS cheer]

430
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:27,083
[KAZAMA] Hm?

431
00:20:27,166 --> 00:20:28,916
What are you doing?

432
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:30,500
N-Nothing.

433
00:20:30,583 --> 00:20:33,708
I was just wondering if you were
scowling down there, that's all.

434
00:20:33,791 --> 00:20:35,291
You're being a butthead.

435
00:20:35,375 --> 00:20:37,083
Who talks to their
king like that?

436
00:20:37,166 --> 00:20:40,833
You admit I won the game, right?

437
00:20:40,916 --> 00:20:42,375
[ROKA]
Of course, Your Highness.

438
00:20:42,458 --> 00:20:48,083
I'm the one who wanted to enter
the tournament, and I lost.

439
00:20:48,166 --> 00:20:52,208
I only ask... that you
take good care of my bag,

440
00:20:52,291 --> 00:20:54,375
like you told me you would.

441
00:20:56,541 --> 00:20:59,208
Or else you'll be
in big trouble!

442
00:21:00,833 --> 00:21:02,375
See ya!

443
00:21:05,875 --> 00:21:08,750
[ROKA] Oh, and next time,
let's do something

444
00:21:08,833 --> 00:21:11,291
that doesn't depend on luck.

445
00:21:18,666 --> 00:21:22,166
[KAZAMA] Heh.
Looks like it was a draw.

446
00:21:28,750 --> 00:21:30,708
[SIOU] You were
transcendent, my rival!

447
00:21:30,791 --> 00:21:31,958
[KAZAMA] Uh--

448
00:21:32,041 --> 00:21:34,166
You can hang onto the
bag for the time being.

449
00:21:34,250 --> 00:21:37,958
We have to do
this again?!

450
00:21:38,041 --> 00:21:38,833
[SIOU laughs]

451
00:21:38,916 --> 00:21:40,250
It goes without saying!

452
00:21:40,333 --> 00:21:43,291
We will continue to be
romantic rivals for Roka

453
00:21:43,375 --> 00:21:45,083
and the bag that we cavorted in.

454
00:21:45,166 --> 00:21:46,875
[KAZAMA yells]

455
00:21:46,958 --> 00:21:48,916
[KAZAMA] What the hell?
Again with the hand?

456
00:21:49,000 --> 00:21:51,458
C'mon, dude, I don't wanna
be your romantic anything!

457
00:21:51,541 --> 00:21:53,416
[SIOU] Love triangle!

458
00:23:23,041 --> 00:23:26,541
[24 BALDIES] Story of Fujou
Academy's 24 Nocturnal Baldies!

459
00:23:26,625 --> 00:23:28,500
[NAKASU groans]

460
00:23:28,583 --> 00:23:29,833
[OHORI]
What're you doing?

461
00:23:29,916 --> 00:23:32,208
We're fellow members of
the 24 Nocturnal Baldies!

462
00:23:32,291 --> 00:23:33,500
[OBORI chuckles]

463
00:23:33,583 --> 00:23:35,083
[OBORI]
Word on the street says

464
00:23:35,166 --> 00:23:37,916
you didn't make it to the final
round in that game tournament.

465
00:23:38,000 --> 00:23:39,916
[BALDY 7A] Yeah, we may've been
on different teams an' all,

466
00:23:40,000 --> 00:23:41,250
but that doesn't matter.

467
00:23:41,333 --> 00:23:43,750
It hurts our rep when
you drop the ball!

468
00:23:43,833 --> 00:23:46,083
Heh. Like you're
one to talk!

469
00:23:46,166 --> 00:23:47,541
Yeah!

470
00:23:47,625 --> 00:23:49,708
Wearing that ridiculous
pompadour wig!

471
00:23:49,791 --> 00:23:52,958
I think you're ashamed
of bein' a baldy!

472
00:23:53,041 --> 00:23:54,000
[TENJIN]
They're right, ya know.

473
00:23:54,083 --> 00:23:55,083
[NAKASU] It's him!

474
00:23:55,166 --> 00:23:58,333
Gentlemen.
When I look in this room,

475
00:23:58,416 --> 00:24:01,125
I see a whole lotta
shiny scalps.

476
00:24:01,208 --> 00:24:03,291
[OHORI] Whoa!
It's "I'm Not Bald" Tenjin!

477
00:24:03,375 --> 00:24:06,000
Tenjin doesn't even
believe he's going bald!

478
00:24:06,083 --> 00:24:07,625
Beat it!

479
00:24:07,708 --> 00:24:11,250
[TENJIN] Hmph. I'm sick and
tired of lying to myself.

480
00:24:11,333 --> 00:24:11,958
[OBORI groans]

481
00:24:12,041 --> 00:24:13,291
[TENJIN] Starting now...

482
00:24:13,375 --> 00:24:16,291
I'm Tenjin the Bald,
of the 24 Nocturnal Baldies!

483
00:24:16,375 --> 00:24:18,416
Tenjin, that's so cool!

484
00:24:18,500 --> 00:24:21,333
Now we're the 25
Nocturnal Baldies!

485
00:24:22,875 --> 00:24:26,250
[OHORI and NAKASU] 
Tenjin? Tenjin!

